<paragraph id="CD2A767151AC5A01A2572877A088FECE" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="E0CF4F1D12B82D0C45897CE34FF69549" LSID="9460942B-EDB9-5900-A5B2-184D03AE7BD3" authority="(form darii Forel, 1911)" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="form darii Forel" baseAuthorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax cf. exilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cf. exilis">Temnothorax cf. exilis (form darii Forel, 1911)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7897D1477D0E605F228C7D83C3976FD3" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FE4D47B376A830B3A534C8129E6DDB3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31F23D300AB834F0C6DF4FE204163D9E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: South Pirin Mt., Kalimantsi vill., 06.04-10.05.2002, pitfall traps, 2 w., leg. M. Langourov; East Rhodopes, Svirachi vill., 22.04.2014, 1 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="9DD794A96CE43A5B4B02501DC39E028B" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D69B35A5FABB2748FF19D4706FCE7A12" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E135D190E2467A9F907190A145ABCF37" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD6E7190C299857B0933C3627858FD0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. This is a common Balkan form of the species belonging to the 
<taxonomicName id="C31F1FBADC31159A6149425EE8D80DDE" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Emery" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax exilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis id="A2CD2C5B55F2F898B856C8F12087F655" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Temnothorax exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. It was described from the vicinity of Izmir in Turkey as var. 
<taxonomicName id="2E7134A66B14EDCAC4D9A38FBD6E9AF8" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax exilis var. darii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="exilis" variety="darii">Temnothorax exilis darii</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F8AB71BB97E3BC64BFA835CF7FE0BFB" author="Forel, A." journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Vaudoise des Sciences Naturelles" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="331 - 400" refId="B7725769" refString="Forel, A., 1911. Fourmis nouvelles ou interessantes. Bulletin de la Societe Vaudoise des Sciences Naturelles 47: 331 - 400" title="Fourmis nouvelles ou interessantes" volume="47" year="1911">Forel 1911</bibRefCitation>
) and synonymised with 
<taxonomicName id="9A533F6BA17F3EA051F8AEA58C14B9BE" genus="T." lsidName="T. exilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis id="CB95349F28BE63E7D4ED73EC122D1BC7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">T. exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="B2D376B2439C1C49AB8CA9418348DC10" author="Baroni Urbani, C." journalOrPublisher="Revue Suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1037 - 1067" refId="B7725624" refString="Baroni Urbani, C., 1971. Studien zur Ameisenfauna Italiens XI. Die Ameisen des Toscanischen Archipels. Betrachtungen zur Herkunft der Inselfaunen. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 78 (56): 1037 - 1067" title="Studien zur Ameisenfauna Italiens XI. Die Ameisen des Toscanischen Archipels. Betrachtungen zur Herkunft der Inselfaunen" volume="78" year="1971">Baroni Urbani (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. It is likely that the Balkan population is not conspecific with true 
<taxonomicName id="37FBF76A9EB9B9B2879727C2CFE2A282" genus="T." lsidName="T. exilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis id="7C7DCB98BFB4A17BB071AAB70FC11F44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">T. exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from the vicinity of Naples in Italy. Until the situation is clarified, we will leave the name of the morphospecies as 
<taxonomicName id="84222C89D2BFBD2BB2552754A664748C" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" form="darii" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax exilis subsp. form" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="form" species="exilis" subSpecies="form">Temnothorax cf. exilis (form darii</taxonomicName>
Forel, 1911).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
